Online Mental Health Consultancy

Welcome to the Online Mental Health Consultancy project, designed to provide mental health resources, consultations, and interactive games for users. The platform offers a range of tools aimed at supporting mental well-being, such as relaxation exercises, cognitive training games, and access to mental health professionals.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project Overview

This project is an online platform designed to offer mental health support through various features. Users can:
Engage in meditation and yoga exercises.
Play interactive games designed to improve cognitive function and reduce stress.
Fill out mental health surveys to monitor their well-being.
Book consultations with mental health professionals.
Learn about mental health topics and self-care practices.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Technologies Used

HTML5: Structure of the web pages.
CSS3: Styling for the user interface (with consultant.css and style.css).
JavaScript: Functionality for interactive games and dynamic content (with files like flappybird.js, memoryGame.js, tetris.js, and script.js).
Python: Backend script for certain functionalities (sih_idea.py).
Web Browser: Supports running HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
File Structure

Here's an overview of the key files used in the project:


/project-folder
│
├── index.html                # Homepage for the platform
├── homepage.html             # Main landing page
├── student.html              # Student consultation page
├── surveys.html              # Mental health surveys page
├── yoga.html                 # Yoga exercises page
├── meditationyoga.html       # Combined meditation and yoga page
├── memory.html               # Memory exercises page
├── tetris.html               # Tetris game page
├── flappybird.html           # Flappy Bird game page
├── games.html                # All games overview page
├── yoga.instructor.html      # Yoga instructor interface
│
├── consultant.css            # CSS for consultant pages
├── style.css                 # Main site-wide CSS
├── flappybird.js             # JavaScript for Flappy Bird game
├── memoryGame.js             # JavaScript for memory game
├── tetris.js                 # JavaScript for Tetris game
├── script.js                 # General script for interactivity
├── sih_idea.py               # Python backend script for certain functionalities
│
└── README.md                 # Project documentation (this file)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Run

To run this project locally:

Clone this repository to your local machine:


git clone https://github.com/your-repo/mental-health-consultancy.git
Navigate to the project directory:

cd mental-health-consultancy
Open any of the HTML files in a web browser (e.g., index.html, homepage.html, etc.) to start exploring the platform.

Example:

open index.html
(Optional) If you have Python installed, you can run the Python script for additional functionality:

python sih_idea.py
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features

1. Interactive Games
Flappy Bird: A fun, stress-relieving game that helps with focus and reaction time.
Memory Game: An exercise that improves memory and cognitive function.
Tetris: A classic game designed to improve cognitive flexibility.
2. Mental Health Resources
Yoga: A variety of yoga exercises and instructor guidance available in the yoga.html and yoga.instructor.html files.
Meditation: A meditation section combined with yoga practices for mental relaxation (available in meditationyoga.html).
3. Consultations
Users can book consultations with mental health professionals through the consultant.css and student.html files.
4. Mental Health Surveys
Users can take surveys to assess their mental health status in the surveys.html file.
5. Dynamic User Interaction
Games and exercises provide immediate feedback, and interactive elements help users engage with the content meaningfully.
6. Responsive Design
The platform is designed to work on different devices, including mobile phones, tablets, and desktop computers.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
